<br>
<br>
The alternative advancement skills instrument mastery (IM) and singing mastery (SM) work as follows.<br>
<br>
IM is an always on, passive skill that adds .2/.4/.6 to all instrument based song mods including voice. This skill, once bought, is on regardless of whether you have an instrument equipped , epic up or are completely naked. The skill is always on and providing the stated mod bonus. im bonus stacks with all other current items and effects including epic, amp and puretone. <br>
NOTE!!!!!<br>
IM no longer helps singing based songs after a recent patch<br>
<br>
<br>
SM works just like IM except it is a .1/.2/.3 modifier for voice only. Again, it is a passive, always on skill that exerts it's bonus mod to voice *only* based songs regardless of any equipment up and **stacks with IM**. sm bonus stacks with all other current items and effects including epic, amp and puretone.<br>
NOTE<br>
sm was patched recently to make the bonus .2/.4/.6 to line up with the nerfed im skill<br>
<br>
<br>
naked with sm3 and im3, the bard has a 1.6 to string, brass, wind and percussion *and now 1.6 to voice only songs*. You still cannot play the invis though since that song requires a wind instrument. <br>
<br>
The gates version of singing and instrument mastery work the same and add another +.2 for a toal of + .8 for someone with aa to burn in bother singing mastery and instrument mastery.<br>
<br>
Cheers!<br>
-EvilModLiq<br>
